
time complexity means - overall execution time of a program--> this defenition is not correct.
cz- execution time may be dependent to the things stated below-
1. algorithm
2. machine- i3,i5,M1 pro etc
3. programmin language- run time : javascript & python (scripted language) >java & C++ > C.

time complexity good(beshi) means the program is good .
it can be calcualted by-

1. Asymtotic method- একটা graph আকা হয়। x অক্ষ বরাবর input & y অক্ষ বরাবর execution time or number of operation লিখা হয়।
                    যার execution time বড় হয় সমান input এর জন্য সেটার time complexity কম। program টা ভালো নয়।

            ig.-->
                calculate the sum from 1 to n.(n<=10 to the power 8)

            process 1-
                        int sum=0;
                        for(int i=1; i<=n ; i++){
                        sum+=i;
                        }
                        return sum;
                 so number of operations= 3*n+3 == n.

                   --> it is dependent to n(input)

            process 2-->
                        int sum=(n*(n+1))/2;
                        return sum;

                 here, number of operations = 4 which is input independent.

              as 4 < n so process 2 is better.

    & this is asymtotic method .

    --> Types of time comlexity analysis & their notations:
    1.  Worst case time complexity= big O -> O(n)  (this is the default case)          (here n is number of operations)
    2.  best case time complexity = big omega -> ohom symbol(n)
    3.  average case time complexity= big theta-> theta symbol(n)

    so process-1 এর time complexity হবে = O(n)     (big o of  n)
    process -2 is O(1)  {এটা O(4) হবে না। O(1) is a constant time algorithm.

    --> question এ time limit দেয়া থাকে । বলা থাকে - time limit is 1 sec
    আসলে 1 second = 10 to the power 8 operations
        2 sec = 2x10^(8) operations

    অর্থাৎ question এ বলে যে এমন একটি code লিখ যা প্রতি সেকেন্ডে 10^8 সংখ্যক operation করতে পাড়বে।

    এখানে একটি বিখ্যাত error - TLE = time limit exceeded
    অর্থাৎ limited time এর বাইরে চলে গেছে।

    some examples of time and space complexity-
    1.
        for loop এ - O(n)

    2.
       nasted for loop -
       a)
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            for(int j=0; j<n; j++){
                sout(print);
            }
        }
        here time complexity is = 3nx3n+1 ==n^2 .

        b)
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            for(int j=0; j<i ; j++){
            sout(print);
            }
        }
        here time complexity is = 3nx3n+1 == n^2 .

        -এখানে , প্রথম for loop (i) এর জন্য approximately n সংখ্যক operation হয়।
        আর, প্রত্যেকবার loop চললে আবার n সংখ্যক operation হয়।
        so, total time complexity is O(n^2).

    3.
        count=0;
        for(int i=0; i<N ; i*=2){
        sout(print);
        }

     relative formula=> n th term N=ar^(n-1) , here n is the number of iterations.
     time complexity is = O(log(n)) ,here base 2 is ignored.

     --> space complexity:
            Extra space or memory used in an algorithm.
            it is same to time complexity.
            But it will count only the extra spaces where INPUT & OUTPUT is not included.
            

